audioContentItems.fileTranscript: Thank you for calling Xfinity Mobile, we appreciate your business. This is (YOUR NAME). May I have your name please?
My name is Danerra Lamburth.
What a beautiful name! Is it okay if I call you by your first name?
Sure, that's fine.
Awesome! How are you doing today, Danerra?
I'm doing fine, thank you. How about yourself?
I'm glad to hear that. I'm doing great as well. Thank you for asking. Tell me, how may I help you today?
I received the SIM card the other day, and as of today, it is still not activated.

Thank you for clarifying that for me! I'd be happy to assist you with activating your new SIM card. To begin the process, I need to access your account first. I'll be asking you a few questions for security purposes; would that be fine?
Sure!
Great! Can you please provide me with your billing address on file?
6000 Hollister St, Apartment 1 8 1 6, Houston, Texas 7 7 0 4 0.
How about the last four digits of the credit or debit card on file?

Thank you, Danerra, for providing all the necessary information to access your account. Your cooperation is appreciated. I was able to pull up your account, and I can see that you have two iPhone devices. May I know the mobile number of the device on which you would like to activate the new SIM card?
To ensure that I got the correct number, which is (560) 346-9876, is that correct?
Yes, that's correct.
Nice! How about the ICCID number of the new SIM card?
Where can I find that?

The ICCID for your Xfinity Mobile SIM card can typically be found printed on the SIM card itself or on the SIM card packaging. It is a unique 20-digit number that identifies your SIM card. If you're unable to locate the ICCID on the SIM card or packaging, you can find it in the settings of your phone once it's inserted. On your iPhone, go to Settings > General > About. The entry titled ICCID is your SIM card number.
I found it! The number is too small on the card. That is 8 9 1 4 8 0 0 0 0 0 9 8 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0.
To confirm, it is 89148000009876543210, am I right?
Yes.

Thank you for confirming it. Let me go ahead and update the new SIM card on your phone. This may take a few minutes to complete the process, and I'll be asking you to reset the network settings of your phone afterwards.
Sure. Take your time.
Okay, here's what I found out, Danerra. Your SIM card is not activated because of the pending order on the account. And this needs to be completed before your SIM card can be activated.
It's been three days; I am confused as to why my phone is still not working, and is this the only reason why?
So please give me a moment while I am working on it. I will let you know once the pending order is completed and to activate the SIM card.
Sure, take your time.

All right, Danerra. I was able to activate and update your new SIM card. Kindly insert the new SIM card and reset the network settings on your phone. Before that, I would like to set your expectation that any saved Wi-Fi networks and passwords will be removed and all paired devices will be unpaired. So, after you reset the network settings, please set up your phone so everything will be connected again. Just go to Settings > General > Reset. Then select "Reset Network Settings" and confirm your choice when prompted. After the reset, your phone will restart. Please test the call functionality afterwards.
I already inserted the SIM card and reset the network settings. My phone is restarting now.
Once your phone is back on, please check the network connectivity and let me know if everything is working as expected.
Sure, I will.

While your phone is restarting, I'd like to express my gratitude for being a valued [Silver, Gold, Platinum, or Premium] customer with Xfinity Rewards. As a loyal customer, you have access to exciting rewards and exclusive benefits. The longer you stay with us, the more rewards you can enjoy. You can conveniently access your rewards anytime through the Xfinity app or by visiting www.xfinity.com/rewards.
Thank you.

Thank you, Danerra! Your loyalty means a lot to us. Don't forget to make the most of the rewards we offer. We have a range of exclusive benefits and perks specifically tailored for customers like you. If you ever have any questions or need assistance in maximizing your rewards, feel free to ask. We're here to help!
I appreciate you sharing that. And I just tested the network, and it's working perfectly now! Thank you for your assistance.
You're most welcome, Danerra. Is there anything else I can assist you with?
No, that was all I needed. I really appreciate your prompt and efficient support.

It's a collaboration with you! Just for a quick recap, you contacted Xfinity today to activate your new SIM card, which is now working as a replacement for the number ending in 9876. Then I asked you to insert the SIM card and reset the network settings. You confirmed that everything is working after testing it.
Thank you so much!
It's been a pleasure taking care of your needs today, and I appreciate your collaboration and patience while we resolved your issue. Thank you, and have a great rest of your day!
Thanks, you too!
This concludes your simulation.
